    <h1>Session 1: Design, Color, Typography</h1>
  
What is Digital Design?
Introduction, laying out questions on principles and process
Objective: Understand the scope of the digital design training

Lecture:

<li>What is digital design in 2022?</li>

<ul>The joys of having this conversation, going beyond "print on screen"</ul>

A very short history of graphic design, web design, UX design, digital product design, architecture and industrial design

What is digital design here?

Designers, project managers, leadership, marketing teams all have to develop a common language

All the creative has to translate across print, social, email, display advertising, website, mobile web

Overlaps with digital marketing, design of products

Research and iteration are the real engine

Research and iteration evolve the framework for decisions

Design tools

Different design scales and outputs: form follows tools, form follows hardware

Who is responsible for the design, and what is being decided?

Color in the digital space
A new world of color
Objective: Understand how color is thought about and handled differently in digital design

Lecture:

Why we pick certain colors

Color is relative "There is no such thing as color, only the interaction of color" (Albers)

Understanding color relationships

Color identification, transparency

The associative nature of color

Color models

CMYK, RGB, HEX, HSB/HSL

Color in CSS, Sketch, Figma

Color in design systems, tokens

Color and accessibility / user control

Contrast as first principle

"Dark mode," "Night shift," and other device-level considerations

Typography (fixed to fluid)
Why the form of type matters, why spacing matters
Objective: Understand how much typography matters in context, what you can and can't control in digital design

Lecture:

Why typography matters more than anything else, why are we spending so much time on it

Form of type: Holding your own under the stress of different form factors

Identity: What am I even looking at

Brief history of type on the web

Type limitations and considerations of email, mobile web

The space of type: Typesetting and usability

Proximity and hierarchy in digital design

Mobile and email specific considerations

Flow to different form factors

Understanding things proportionally rather than in absolute terms

What is an em, how does this all get coded

Typesetting and accessibility

Typesetting and design systems

